

Describe a time when you receive money as a gift

This topic reminds me of my 20th birthday, which was one of the most memorable moments in my life. It happened about four years ago, but I can still remember it very clearly.

At that time, I was extremely busy with exams, so I didn’t plan any celebration at all. In fact, I almost forgot it was my birthday. But my roommates surprised me in the most thoughtful way.

I remember coming back home in the evening after a long and exhausting day. I was just about to go to bed when I opened the door and suddenly heard everyone shouting “Happy Birthday.” They had prepared a small cake and decorated the room, which completely caught me off guard.

What touched me the most was that they also gave me an envelope with some money inside. All of them had contributed, and it came to around one million dong. It might not seem like a lot, but at that time, I was a student and a bit short on money, so it really meant a lot to me.

More than the money itself, it was the thought and effort behind it that made me feel so grateful. I instantly forgot how tired I was and just felt incredibly happy.

Even now, whenever I think about that moment, it brings a smile to my face. It reminded me how lucky I am to have such caring friends.